	<h2 class="story">
		

		

		
		

		

		

		

		<span id="title-173586102" class="story-title"> <a   href="//tech.slashdot.org/story/24/04/19/2219216/british-columbia-bans-level-3-and-above-autonomous-cars">British Columbia Bans Level 3 and Above Autonomous Cars</a> <span class=" no extlnk"><a class="story-sourcelnk" href="https://www.thedrive.com/news/self-driving-cars-banned-in-british-columbia"  title="External link - https://www.thedrive.com/news/self-driving-cars-banned-in-british-columbia" target="_blank"> (thedrive.com) </a></span></span>

		
		
		<!--<span class="comments commentcnt-173586102" >41</span>-->
		

		
		<!-- comment bubble -->
		
			<span class="comment-bubble"><a href="//tech.slashdot.org/story/24/04/19/2219216/british-columbia-bans-level-3-and-above-autonomous-cars#comments" title="">41</a></span>
		
	</h2>
	<div class="details" id="details-173586102">
		<span class="story-details">
		<span class="story-views">
			<span class="sodify" onclick="firehose_set_options('color', 'red')" title="Filter Firehose to entries rated red or better"></span><span class="icon-beaker pop1 " alt="Popularity" title="Filter Firehose to entries rated red or better" onclick="firehose_set_options('color', 'red')"><span></span></span> 
		</span>
		</span>
		<span class="story-byline">
	
				
			Posted
				by 
		
		
			
				  <a href="https://twitter.com/BeauHD" rel="nofollow">BeauHD</a>
			
		
		

		
		
		<time id="fhtime-173586102" datetime="on Saturday April 20, 2024 @09:00AM">on Saturday April 20, 2024 @09:00AM</time>
		
		
			 from the <span class="dept-text">getting-ready-for-the-future</span> dept.
		
		</span>
	</div>
</header>

<div class="body" id="fhbody-173586102">
	
		
	

	
		
		<div id="text-173586102" class="p">
			
		 	
				New submitter <a href="/~Baloo+Uriza">Baloo Uriza</a> writes: <i>In a rare display of sanity in the automotive space, British Columbia has <a href="https://www.thedrive.com/news/self-driving-cars-banned-in-british-columbia">banned autonomous cars from its highways</a> after years of watching autonomous cars <a href="https://tech.slashdot.org/story/23/09/03/1722242/cruise-disputes-report-its-robotaxi-blocked-an-ambulance-carrying-patient-who-later-died">hamper emergency response efforts</a> in California and outright <a href="https://tech.slashdot.org/story/18/03/19/1736231/self-driving-uber-car-kills-arizona-woman-in-first-fatal-crash-involving-pedestrian">kill a pedestrian</a> in Arizona. Let's hope this regulatory trend continues and moves into the human space by pulling licenses of drivers with a known history of poor driving.</i> In the shared article, The Drive notes that the ban only applies to self-driving vehicles that exceed a Society of Automotive Engineers (SAE) autonomy rating of Level 2.
[A full breakdown of each of the levels can be found <a href="https://www.synopsys.com/automotive/autonomous-driving-levels.html">here</a>.] The ban is part of an update to B.C.'s Motor Vehicle Act that went into effect on April 5, 2024 and includes possible consequences of a max penalty of $2,000 (CAD) in fines and up to six months of prison time. Importantly, the ban could change as autonomous driving tech evolves in the coming years.
<br> <br>
Since the ban doesn't affect Level 2 vehicles, Tesla owners who use Autopilot and FSD, as well as Ford and GM vehicle owners with BlueCruise and Super Cruise, will be exempt. In fact, there are currently no Level 3 autonomous vehicles for sale in Canada.<br>
		 	
		</div>

		

		

		
			
		
	</div>
